00:27:47.079 --> 00:27:49.980
And you might see those dot underscore files.

00:27:49.980 --> 00:27:50.900
Why are those there?

00:27:50.900 --> 00:27:55.450
Well those are resource forks that
the Mac has copied onto that server.

00:27:55.450 --> 00:28:00.740
Now when the Mac copies that file, because that file
system didn't, doesn't have support for resource forks.

00:28:00.740 --> 00:28:06.279
But when the Mac sees those, and it copies those
files back, it's going to take that dot underscore file,

00:28:06.279 --> 00:28:09.200
recombine it with the original file when it brings it back

00:28:09.200 --> 00:28:13.920
onto the Mac file system, so it
